Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the properties of a logic system. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is also likely as the paper extends First Order Logic with inclusion dependencies, which are commonly used in database systems. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper discusses the properties of a logic system that can be used in knowledge representation and reasoning. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the properties of relations, which can be represented as graphs or other data structures. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also less likely but possible as the paper discusses the complexity of the logic system and its equivalence to Fixed Point Logic.
